examples: Coordinate terms: singlet, couplet, triplet, quadruplet, tetraplet, pentuplet, quintuplet, septuplet, octuplet, nonuplet, decuplet, centuplet, multiplet

entries.meaning: One of a group of six persons or animals born from the same mother during the same birth.

definitionGroups.group: (music) A group of six notes played in the time of four.

entries.meaning: (music, proscribed) A group of six notes played in the time of four, with accents on the first, third and fifth notes.
(music, proscribed) A group of six notes played in the time of four, with accents on the first and fourth notes; a double triplet.
(music, proscribed) A group of six notes played in the time of four, with an accent only on the first note.
